# Security & CSP rules (MANDATORY)

- Never generate inline JavaScript.
  - No <script>...</script> blocks in HTML.
  - No onclick=, onchange=, onsubmit=, or any inline event handlers.

- Never use eval(), new Function(), or dynamically constructed code execution.

- All JavaScript must be placed in external .js or .ts files and loaded via <script src="...">.

- Event handling must always use addEventListener() or framework equivalents.

- Code must be compatible with a strict Content-Security-Policy:
  script-src 'self' 'nonce-*'
  style-src 'self' (inline styles discouraged)

- If inline scripts are unavoidable, explicitly ask the user before using CSP nonces.

- Prefer progressive enhancement and unobtrusive JavaScript.

- Any generated HTML must pass CSP validation with NO 'unsafe-inline' or 'unsafe-eval'.
